🧠 The Extracted Pattern (General Form)

Preserve core invariants while evolving expression under strict constraints

That’s the whole thing.

⸻

🔧 Break it into reusable components

1) Invariant Core (what must NOT change)
	•	Identity
	•	Function
	•	Feel / personality

👉 This is the “Kanto DNA”

⸻

2) Expression Layer (what CAN change)
	•	Style
	•	detail level
	•	presentation

👉 This is where evolution happens safely

⸻

3) Constraint Profile (the guardrails)

These prevent drift:
	•	simplicity over complexity
	•	one idea over many
	•	clarity over novelty
	•	coherence over expansion

👉 This is what keeps things “on-theme”

⸻

4) Trajectory Lock (direction of evolution)

Not just constraints, but direction:
	•	refine, don’t reinvent
	•	compress, don’t expand
	•	clarify, don’t decorate

👉 Evolution = sharpening, not mutation

⸻

🧭 The Formula (portable)

You can reuse this anywhere:

New Version = Invariant Core + (Refined Expression constrained by original trajectory)

⸻

🔁 Apply it outside Pokémon

🏢 Product Design
	•	Keep core function
	•	simplify UI
	•	remove features instead of adding

⸻

🧠 Ideas / Philosophy (Pantheon 👀)
	•	keep core concepts
	•	rename + clarify
	•	remove mythic overload
	•	make it teachable

⸻

🎬 Movies / Storytelling
	•	preserve archetypes
	•	modernize pacing/visuals
	•	don’t overload with subplots

⸻

👔 Personal Identity / Brand
	•	keep your core traits
	•	refine how you present
	•	reduce noise, increase signal

⸻

⚠️ What breaks the pattern
	•	adding too many new ideas
	•	chasing novelty over coherence
	•	losing the original “feel”
	•	complexity creep

That’s how things become:

“same franchise, different soul”

